715888f-a.text:
George Washington High School is located at 549 Audubon Avenue at West 193rd Street in the Fort George neighborhood of the Washington Heights, Manhattan, New York City.

Board of Education, N.Y.C.
May 6, 1926
715888f-a.folder: Academy Street & Vermilyea Avenue, Manhattan, NY

723777f-a.text:
Vermilyea Avenue, west side, north from Academy Street, showing school children out at recess time.
The apartment building on the N.W. corner was erected between 1918 and 1922.  66 and 72 Vermileay Avenue, the two buildings in the middle of the block, are a little older.
October 26, 1927.
P.L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
